original: Lindell, Harald, landskamrerare, Visby, f. 1/2/93 i Norrköping av civil-ing. August L. o. Alice Nordström. G. 21 m. Ingrid Johnzon. Barn: Göran H:son f. 23, arkit. SAR. — Jur. kand. i Upps. 19. Andre länsbokh. i Värml. län 22, förste dito 29, länsassessor i Kopparb. län 36, landskamr. i Gotl. län sed. 42. Innehade olika kommun, uppdrag i Karlstad, v. ordf. i direkt, f. S :t Olofs sjukh. o. Gotl. läns kristidsstyr. 43’, ordf. i styr. f. Riksbankens avd:kont. i Visby 47. RNO.
translated: Lindell, Harald, provincial treasurer, Visby, born on February 1, 1893 in Norrköping, to civil engineer August L. and Alice Nordström. Married on the 21st to Ingrid Johnzon. Children: Göran H:son, born in 1923, architect, SAR. Graduated with a law degree from Uppsala University in 1919. Second county accountant in Värmland county from 1922, first county accountant from 1929, county assessor in Kopparberg county from 1936, provincial treasurer in Gotland county since 1942. Held various municipal positions in Karlstad, vice chairman of the board for St. Olof's Hospital and Gotland county crisis management team in 1943, chairman of the board for the Visby branch of the Riksbank in 1947. Awarded the Royal Order of the North Star (RNO).

awards.name: Royal Order of the North Star
